    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-09-20T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-09-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="450"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d450">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">861.00/5245: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">President <persName corresp="#p_WW1" type="from"
                            >Wilson</persName> to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Los Angeles</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-09-20">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 20, 1919</hi>
                        </date>.<lb/>[Received September 21, 12:44 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>I fully approve of your proposals with regard to the Czechoslovak forces in
                    Siberia and with regard to furnishing such supplies as are available to the
                    forces under <persName corresp="#p_KAAV1">Kolchak</persName>, and authorize you
                    to show this telegram to the Secretary of the Treasury, the Secretary of War and
                    the Chairman of the Shipping Board.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_WW1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Woodrow Wilson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
